text.tspan: Associate to each point its open cover
Take all points of the form {x0}*Y along with their open rectangles
For each element in {x0}*Y, project covering rectangle to Y...
For each {x0}*Y, project to Y and find finite subcover
Pick an open neighbourhood around each point
inside the open cover associated to it. Pick the neighbourhood
such that the neighbourhood is a product of X * Y
To find bottleneck at x0, (instead of min), we project rectangles of the
finite subcover of Y to X and intersect all of the projections.
Intersection of finite number of open sets is finite, so the bottleneck
is an open set. the open-ness of the bottleneck is used later to extract
a finite number of bottlenecks [using the compactness of X].
Consider all bottlenecks of all {x0} * Y
We are done. We have a finite number of X intervals,
with a finite number of boxes per interval. Each interval in X
cover Y * {open set}. We have a finite number of {open rectangles}
U Y * {open set} = Y *{ U open set} = Y * X
From these rectangles we can extract a finite subcover,
since each rectangle is associate to an open set.
